I'm super into this. It's simple, it's inexplicable, it's horrifying; the fact that it's traumatic and messy and defies consensus reality without being especially dangerous in and of itself is refreshing. There's just enough here to get my imagination going about what could be causing this - is it phantom overlay from another universe where things have gone very wrong? An effort by some kind of rodent god to make people of its own? Just a nonsensical glitch in reality? I love the old-school feel here of a memorable, stimulating, simple-yet-baffling weird thing.







